observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
a. create an Inventory Committee for the one-time cleansing of PPE in 2026;
b. require the General Services Officer, Municipal Accountant and the duly created Inventory Committee to follow the procedural guidelines on the one-time cleansing of PPE prescribed under COA Circular No. 2020-006 such as (1) Preliminary activities prior to the conduct of inventory taking; (2) Inventory taking; (3) Reconciliation of inventory count per RPCPPE with property and accounting records; (4) Disposition procedures for non-existing/missing PPEs; (5) Procedures in the derecognition of non-existing/missing PPEs without available record of accountability; and (6) Accounting entries and disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements.

Based on the foregoing, we recommended the Municipal Mayor to:
a. Prioritize the conduct of one-time cleansing of PPE accounts as soon as possible by creating an Inventory Committee composed of adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory in three months or less; 
b. Instruct the Inventory Committee to prepare a PIP to include the specific name of committee members, with the cut-off date and the schedule specifying the dates and locations of the inventory taking activities from start up to the targeted completion of the physical inventory which shall be within three months or less and duly approved by the Municipal Mayor to be submitted to the Audit Team at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled inventory taking activities; 
c. Require the newly created Inventory Committee, GSO and the Accounting Office to perform the preliminary activities by preparation of appropriate reports such as latest RPCPPE, Inventory Count Form and PPELCs and reconcile their records before the actual physical inventory; and 
d. Provide transportation by equipment and other necessary tools for the implementation of the one-time cleansing.

