a. The Inventory Committee, immediately after complete physical count, to reconcile inventory results with property and accounting records; 
b. The Property and Accounting units to perform reconciliation of the PPE balance particularly on the noted difference of P69,125,576.18 and make the necessary adjustments/recording of entries, if any; 
c. The Inventory Committee to ensure that all counted items are properly specified and identified detailing physical attributes and location; 
d. The Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to the Financial Statements the results of reconciliation of RPCPPE and accounting records as well as the amount of PPE items, if any, without available supporting documents; and 
